                    <span>This is an excellent expostion of the Win32  operating system from a system programmers perspective. The author takes the approach of exposing the operating system by delving into the mysterious realm of VxD device drivers.  This is an important and I think well considered approach.  By descibing 32 bit device drivers development two important goals are met in this book.  First the Win95 core OS is well descibed and second, the products of the exposition with the example code provide usefull starting tools.  The style is readable and in some parts intertaining given the subject.  I bought a second copy of the book knowing that whoever borrows it won't be returning it.</span>
                  
              
